<paragraph id="D55854A1F2C1C41B23E921F2A214CA11" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<taxonomicName id="7DAA9EBC9365EBC552F7D544845856DA" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Castrida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Castrida</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1866: 300. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="750B2DDDD67F6C09DB888EF16F1D2B68" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1826" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Calosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sayi">
<emphasis id="6E0B8D51A3C853912BB0517F847727F2" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Calosoma sayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1826 by monotypy. Etymology. Unknown [feminine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="33BFC6A00E46642181AA2FDB3885A129" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<taxonomicName id="8B7D51E6AFDE67F691B713C68A989B7A" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Camedula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Camedula</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1866: 304. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="55CB5CF272CFC470D15744635E1BBD3C" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Calosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipenne">
<emphasis id="566E4ED970988B382BB5587E22143104" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Calosoma rufipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831 designated by 
<normalizedToken id="E71A20A05A109E627CDB246CF4D13781" originalValue="Géhin">Gehin</normalizedToken>
(1885: xxxi). Note. The first type species designation for 
<taxonomicName id="35A8DC4C1D293E2FB5FE3FEBE9EBBB15" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Camedula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED18EE48A7D9276110D5A0FAAFD2A90F" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Camedula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky is that of 
<taxonomicName id="6ED14BF26685362274D6298279CE8F7E" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Calosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabratum">
<emphasis id="3246D1C210A7FA23D243BFD0CA3CDBCA" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Calosoma glabratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831 as selected by 
<normalizedToken id="7A9C5B414E779C5EF0717B088806FDFB" originalValue="Géhin">Gehin</normalizedToken>
(1876b: 114). This species has been accepted as the type species by Jeannel (1940: 199) and Gidaspow (1959: 256). However, Breuning (1928a: 93) accepted 
<taxonomicName id="0C35F3CE4918A0A702AB7EB56774BD05" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Calosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipenne">
<emphasis id="24116C6961092E303C38A9CB29F724F8" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Calosoma rufipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831 as type species following 
<normalizedToken id="C25C62D3BE7AE49FFF1B1C1FD0B59E73" originalValue="Géhin">Gehin</normalizedToken>
(1885: xxxi) and this species is currently recognized as the type species (e.g., Lorenz 1998: 59, Lorenz 2005: 57). As discussed by Bousquet (2002b: 11-12), the best solution to preserve nomenclatural stability is to refer the case to the Commission in order to maintain 
<taxonomicName id="9E22C3A2B532749E9F4023E18DC52F4B" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Calosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipenne">
<emphasis id="70A685960C7D86E5C7832AC3368EDC7A" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Calosoma rufipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean as type species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D858E8090328B624E4E07ED94E9080C7" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<taxonomicName id="1A7242AA605C37411EE98B866E17B229" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Callistriga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Callistriga</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1866: 307. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="67C1E7EDE12481E10B659D8F4841ABDF" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alternans">
<emphasis id="6E34673ADD28157C0B0CF1299A18A5F3" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Carabus alternans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fabricius, 1792 designated by 
<normalizedToken id="3989A49E736041AA6A5733FDD1B24ABC" originalValue="Géhin">Gehin</normalizedToken>
(1876b: 114). Synonymy established by Csiki (1927: 11).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="600F2FEEC30F3FACC0AEC4EAC8B6F649" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<taxonomicName id="5CA3704988839E6AF5014390A699075C" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calamata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Calamata</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1866: 307. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="3BE1072CA9EB97C08CFDBEF91ED27B94" authorityName="Motschulsky" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Calamata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugata">
<emphasis id="2F2798F6A47C47711AEFEE055BBAD17B" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Calamata rugata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1866 (= 
<taxonomicName id="F6B8570642FC5AF162302E3A48C09CF2" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1830" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Calosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="alternans" subSpecies="granulatum">
<emphasis id="823AE9268DDE88AE69E85E265DE75768" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Calosoma alternans granulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Perty, 1830) by monotypy. Synonymy established by Csiki (1927: 11).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA2FC7802E5650E90BC9EB33A986EB73" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<taxonomicName id="BE19D66F33D6C63B58FAE5DA2BFD65D6" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1928" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Microcalosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Microcalosoma</taxonomicName>
Breuning, 1927: 146. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="ABF7E6FC7917C2E23773828BA5772330" authorityName="Mutchler" authorityYear="1925" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Calosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linelli">
<emphasis id="B2344A92DEC0DC1A9FC914451DE37D6C" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Calosoma linelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mutchler, 1925 by monotypy. Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="546EDC07BADE62CA11D82A1065252516" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">micros</emphasis>
(small) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="EC21656F9DAB368C38159FB92B93DD33" authorityName="Weber" authorityYear="1801" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Calosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8D8F9ACC1878C6DEDEDCD92285DCF222" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Calosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="17B735CAB10B5B5E0B5D299669F03BC7" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">q.v</emphasis>
.] [neuter].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DE677B3A11CA29C9FB0B8929E9356B32" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<taxonomicName id="0E33BFA1E0298519B2FE39E18DC2DBFC" authorityName="Lapouge" authorityYear="1929" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acampalita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Acampalita</taxonomicName>
Lapouge, 1929b: 9. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="270C3B63EBF42B7A5CE83DE21BC7E04E" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Calosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vagans">
<emphasis id="B25F7AE38723BFDF41AC8BD29EE4C068" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Calosoma vagans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831 by subsequent monotypy in Lapouge (1931: 418). Synonymy established by Jeannel (1940: 89). Etymology. From the Greek prefix 
<emphasis id="91EED1555E9CE2901A16C6E127AF61E0" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">a</emphasis>
- (privative) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="ABF7DE839CFC19CCD81977EFFFB1A3C0" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Campalita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B2EB59E6648ADB9909EDB12FB8DA0BED" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Campalita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[feminine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="537BBBD4ACD68412874987D74E208DBD" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<taxonomicName id="E11E2B2C55EB82CD2280611CA145C540" authorityName="Lapouge" authorityYear="1929" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Catastriga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Catastriga</taxonomicName>
Lapouge, 1929b: 9. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="6411E5E0201D0382282435A5D99F3A35" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1869" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Calosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trapezipenne">
<emphasis id="48C718719C0406A244B75B1B51CC9578" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Calosoma trapezipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 1869 by subsequent monotypy in Lapouge (1931: 418). Synonymy established by Gidaspow (1959: 240).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1EAADE11A89FBCA806BC77210FCDB4E3" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<taxonomicName id="364BDC2E239D775475BA91EAB5C8AF32" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1940" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Caludema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Caludema</taxonomicName>
Jeannel, 1940: 89, 91. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="AA67650F933ED23F256943E8E902953D" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Calosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipenne">
<emphasis id="C33321454E4B4B6A0E3FEE8FB35C3A19" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Calosoma rufipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831 by original designation. Synonymy established by Gidaspow (1963: 289). Etymology. Anagram of the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="54EEF17AA22F7736612CE92ECD884211" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Camedula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4F17EFBC9F2A653D8E5E1923126FEFE6" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Camedula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="09285BD731E25473898E223D7C10F13D" italics="true" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">q.v</emphasis>
.] [neuter].
</paragraph>
